examples: A peach and an apricot? What's the diff?

entries.meaning: (computing) Any program which compares two files or sets of files and outputs a description of the differences between them.
(computing) The output of a diff program, a diff file.
examples: I didn't want to waste people's time telling them things they already knew. It's more efficient just to give them the diffs.

entries.meaning: (automotive) Abbreviation of differential: the differential gear in an automobile.
(medicine) Abbreviation of differential: differential of types of white blood cell in a complete blood count.

verbs.description: diff (third-person singular simple present diffs, present participle diffing, simple past and past participle diffed)

entries.meaning: (transitive, computing) To run a diff program on (files or items) so as to produce a description of the differences between them, as for a patch file.
(transitive, computing) To compare two files or other objects, manually or otherwise.
